 * Error. Band structure and exact exchange are requested at the same time,
 * but the keyword 'exx_band_structure_version' is not set.
 * We require that this keyword be set explicitly to make sure that our
 * users understand a specific aspect of the current band structure
 * calculation framework for hybrid density functionals with FHI-aims.
 * This has been used successfully by many groups for published work,
 * but please be sure to understand the current usage. 
 * 
 * There are two variants of the band structure calculation for hybrid
 * density functionals: 
 * 
 * --- exx_band_structure_version 1 :
 *     This version is evaluated in a real-space formalism. It is fast
 *     and the preferred version. HOWEVER, it does require a sufficiently
 *     dense 'k_grid' to be used for the preceding s.c.f. cycle.
 *     If the 'k_grid used for s.c.f. is NOT dense enough, the real-
 *     space approach will produce bands that are OBVIOUSLY incorrect.
 *     You cannot miss this - they won't look 'slightly' correct. In
 *     that case, please try to increase the 'k_grid' parameters used
 *     for the s.c.f. cycle. In particular, please avoid k_grid dimensions 
 *     of '1' (one) in any dimension. We apologize for this inconvenience.
 *     On the bright side, if you use exx_band_structure_version 1 
 *     correctly, it will give reliable results without much overhead.
 * 
 * --- exx_band_structure_version 2 : 
 *     This version is evaluated completely in reciprocal space and does
 *     not have any problems with sparse s.c.f. 'k_grid' settings. 
 *     HOWEVER: exx_band_structure_version 2 is computationally VERY expensive.
 *     Please only use it for verification and/or if, for some reason, you
 *     cannot make exx_band_structure_version 1 work at all. The time and memory
 *     demand of exx_band_structure_version 2 is very significant.
 *     Ideally, at least work with a low number of k-points within band segments,
 *     for example, 11 or less.
